==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[neahgebur|nēahġebūr]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'neɪbə/

===Noun===
'''neighbour''' (''plural:'' '''[[neighbours]]''')
# A person living on [[adjacen]]t or [[nearby]] land.
#: ''My '''neighbour''' has an annoying cat''
#: ''They're our '''neighbours''' across the street''

